Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.29,0:28:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.29,0:28:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,was a clinical,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.29,0:28:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,was clinical science,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.29,0:28:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,not academic science,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.29,0:28:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,academic science,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.05,0:28:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.05,0:28:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.05,0:28:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,clinical science,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.05,0:28:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,starts,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.05,0:28:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,really,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.05,0:28:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,at 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.05,0:28:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,academic science,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.22,0:28:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.38,0:28:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,between a clinician,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.38,0:28:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.38,0:28:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,over 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.38,0:28:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and 100,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.38,0:28:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite remarkable,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.38,0:28:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.38,0:28:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,my witnessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.85,0:28:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.85,0:28:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the huge,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.85,0:28:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,another piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.85,0:28:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,some doctors,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.85,0:28:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,got tremendous results,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.85,0:28:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with just about everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.85,0:28:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,even the most impossible cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.85,0:28:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and other doctors,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.85,0:28:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,who are academically,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.85,0:28:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,equally,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.85,0:28:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,well-trained,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.85,0:28:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,got relatively,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.85,0:28:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,comparably,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.85,0:28:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,miserable results,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.85,0:28:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.85,0:28:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.85,0:28:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of the healer,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.85,0:28:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the healing,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.89,0:28:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,this,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.89,0:28:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.89,0:28:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.89,0:28:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.89,0:28:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.89,0:28:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of caring,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.89,0:29:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for your patient,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.89,0:29:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing them,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.89,0:29:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.89,0:29:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and being dedicated,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.89,0:29:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.89,0:29:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is why,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.89,0:29:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,some doctors,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.89,0:29:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,some doctors have rather incredible practices. Intention. So these are the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.13,0:29:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness and we calibrated them. They're pretty much
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.73,0:29:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional throughout man's history, the alignment. In Columbia Psychoanalytic
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.60,0:29:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,these were called the emergency emotions and these are the welfare emotions. These
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.08,0:29:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are the ones that bring you in to see the doctor and these are the ones that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.10,0:29:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,take you out. I never saw any patients who suffered from serenity. Never did.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.20,0:29:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact their problem was they were allergic to serenity, you know. Serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.44,0:30:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is the last thing. A lot of people don't like serenity and although it's, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.16,0:30:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we consider it an axiom in spiritual evolution, serenity frankly
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.72,0:30:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly, is not sought by a large percentage of the population,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.83,0:30:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,probably the majority.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.46,0:30:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The majority of the population really is not interested in serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.11,0:30:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because if they have the option, they turn it down all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.18,0:30:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They turn it down all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.61,0:30:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll pick an argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.29,0:30:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The TV shows are full of blood and murder and conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.71,0:30:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So how to reach a state of serenity in a sort of chaotic appearing world, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.51,0:30:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people of all different levels of consciousness and animal life, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.70,0:30:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is all thrown in together.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.70,0:30:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, to get along here with people who are just like that is a snap, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.83,0:31:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang out with people that calibrate 350, your life is joyful.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.11,0:31:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They're cheerful, helpful, they volunteer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.79,0:31:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the humanitarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.42,0:31:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So if everybody was right here at 350, this would be a great place.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.33,0:31:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Serenity would be sort of an automatic consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.77,0:31:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, what's happened is that in the world, 80% or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.46,0:31:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,80% are below the level of truth, below this level.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.35,0:31:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're living in a world sort of like the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.88,0:31:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There are lots of sharks and octopuses and people out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.79,0:31:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.48,0:31:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the butterfly fish are up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.48,0:31:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.38,0:31:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.88,0:31:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's why it's maximum karmic benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.06,0:31:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we have an infinite series of choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.02,0:31:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we can undo negative karma and gain positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.30,0:32:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.80,0:32:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said, how fortunate to be born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.86,0:32:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.36,0:32:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How rare to be born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.95,0:32:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You think of all living things, the chances of being born a human is minute, minute, minuscule.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.89,0:32:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Point oh, oh, oh, oh, something.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.96,0:32:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then to be spiritually aligned on top of that is rarer still.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.40,0:32:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And to choose to strive for enlightenment is the rarest of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.31,0:32:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarest of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.55,0:32:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Practically never happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.00,0:32:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we calibrated, the desire for enlightenment occurs in less than one in 10 million people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.11,0:32:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Less than one in 10 million persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.11,0:32:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Less than one in 10 million persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.11,0:32:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask them, say, what's your greatest ambition to achieve in your lifetime, they
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.01,0:32:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,would say enlightenment, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.27,0:32:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So consequently, it has been rare over time, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.27,0:32:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.29,0:32:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've got this calibrated scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.29,0:32:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I just want to say something about, turn off the light a second, about kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.72,0:33:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the place of it in research, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.01,0:33:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a research tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.64,0:33:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Institute for Consciousness Research.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.92,0:33:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's based on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.92,0:33:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The research's done using kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.92,0:33:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, kinesiology is just like a tool, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.92,0:33:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a thermometer or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.92,0:33:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not supposed to genuflect in front of the thermometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.92,0:33:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a handy, rough tool, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.92,0:33:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not perfected.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.92,0:33:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the ultimate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.92,0:33:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's quick and handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.07,0:33:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't, you know, go through a computer to decide what you're going to have for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.26,0:33:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Just say, well, I'll have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.26,0:33:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.26,0:33:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My cholesterol's maybe a little high.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.26,0:33:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lot of fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.26,0:33:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's not a great big deal, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.26,0:33:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to make a big deal out of kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.26,0:33:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It was useful in research.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.26,0:33:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I made the mistake of sharing it with the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.26,0:33:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the mistake I made in the first book, Harvest is for Us, I presumed that everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.26,0:33:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,could do kinesiology, you know, with relative ease or relative accuracy, and then discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.26,0:33:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was a good idea to do it in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.26,0:33:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.26,0:33:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.40,0:33:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.40,0:33:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.40,0:33:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.40,0:33:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.40,0:33:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.35,0:33:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.35,0:33:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.49,0:33:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.49,0:33:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.49,0:34:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.49,0:34:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.49,0:34:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.49,0:34:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.49,0:34:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.49,0:34:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.49,0:34:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.49,0:34:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.49,0:34:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.48,0:34:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.48,0:34:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.48,0:34:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.48,0:34:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.48,0:34:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I used the perfect method to build this book, Harvest is for Us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.48,0:34:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I presumed that everybody could do kinesiology, you know, with relative ease or relative accuracy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.48,0:34:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and then discovered later that it's only people who calibrate 200 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.67,0:34:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In America, 49% of the population calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.15,0:34:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So there goes 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.26,0:34:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I found out about 10%, people for some karmic reason are unable to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.05,0:34:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then on top of that, your motivation has to be intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.90,0:34:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have two integrous people who both calibrate over 200, and it can't be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.76,0:34:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,stated as a question, it's made as a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.23,0:34:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be able to pose a detached scientific question, that is also rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.69,0:35:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So kinesiology is very useful in research, and the reason that we wrote Truth Versus
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.65,0:35:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood, because it realizes a lot of people don't have the time or the expertise, and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.26,0:35:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like riding a bicycle, some people just don't have it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.44,0:35:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Or horseback, I gave up on horses, you know, I got thrown about 18 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.94,0:35:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Horses are not my way, my path to salvation, and I gave them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.59,0:35:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to take the word of others that are experienced with it, that the figures
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.82,0:35:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,are reasonably accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.94,0:35:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now again, we don't claim infallibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.61,0:35:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's nowhere in the books do I claim infallibility, in a sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.94,0:35:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore there's some errors, and there are some discrepancies in some of the calibrations,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.65,0:35:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,partly due to my progressive age, partly due to the fact that Truth Versus Falsehood had
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.46,0:35:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,12 or 14 or 15 manuscript revisions, and there's typos and things.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.57,0:35:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So occasionally there will be something where I say the rhinoceros calibrates to something
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.01,0:36:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,here, and then I say it calibrates to something there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.67,0:36:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But then we find some other things, too, that you can get different, specific calibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.98,0:36:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.59,0:36:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I say, I make a list of good fatherhood, and then here's Joe Blow, he calibrates at
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.19,0:36:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,540, third father.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.61,0:36:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if I put here authors, and I put Joe Blow, because he also wrote a book, he may
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.90,0:36:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,only be 205, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.46,0:36:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So in what context do they calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.13,0:36:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.80,0:36:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.67,0:36:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the latest thing we've learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.05,0:36:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We did know already, of course, that what you hold in mind can be held in various ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.15,0:36:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say, what does your mother calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.09,0:36:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean the memory of her, visual, auditory, emotionals?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.80,0:36:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,People track stimuli.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.28,0:36:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are primarily visual, some are auditory, some are feeling types, some are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.19,0:37:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,tactile.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.21,0:37:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.76,0:37:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And at what age, see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.53,0:37:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you might get different calibrations of your mother, depending on one time you remember
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.11,0:37:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how you felt when you came home after school, and you could smell apple pie cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.40,0:37:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you might think of her at another time, visually, mad at you, saying you're
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.82,0:37:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,holding, so it depends on what context you hold her, what stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.36,0:37:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I just want to say the calibrations are not written in stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.11,0:37:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not written in stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.92,0:37:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They're to give us a guideline.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.96,0:37:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does the calibrated number mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.86,0:37:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What it really means is it's an abstraction of an enormous complexity that gives us pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.78,0:37:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,much a generality, although the number is numerical.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.61,0:37:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's to give you a feeling for where that is, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.21,0:38:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When we said 350, 350 is a level, a characterizing number.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.98,0:38:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's characterized by goodwill, helpfulness, positive, optimist, people who rescue teams,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.76,0:38:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.76,0:38:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Firemen, rescue divers, and people like that, that we all admire.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.07,0:38:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all at least 350 around.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.11,0:38:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What they represent is the willingness to serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.38,0:38:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what we're trying to convey, is the general feeling of that field, and of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.90,0:38:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,course.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.94,0:38:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, spiritual students, we're concerned with what is the long-term spiritual significance
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.28,0:38:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of a number.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.19,0:38:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Very rarely does a small difference make any difference, unless you're doing micro-research.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.94,0:38:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're doing micro-research, then, then the specific number becomes more important.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.01,0:39:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you have to be careful to always hold the same context in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.73,0:39:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to talk about mother, then disciple.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.21,0:39:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then decide it's going to be how mother looked, and every time you ask about mother, or you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.92,0:39:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,picture mother, don't go to a feeling state.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.86,0:39:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So research requires, then, more careful control of the context, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.55,0:39:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But again, small discrepancies usually don't mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.86,0:39:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other thing is, in reading, you know, Truth Versus Falsehood, I notice some people
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.94,0:39:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,get lost in the trees and miss the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.09,0:39:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what's the purpose of writing Truth Versus Falsehood?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.38,0:39:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.38,0:39:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.34,0:39:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to document forever the calibrated number of everything on the planet, but because
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.46,0:39:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it leads to a realization of truth and the pathway to truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.88,0:39:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the overall thrust, you see, of the work, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.84,0:39:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So keep a balanced view that kinesiology is not the be-all, end-all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.76,0:39:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.76,0:39:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's prone to error.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.30,0:40:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be prone to error.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.46,0:40:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you learn how to do it just like you do writing a bison.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.38,0:40:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Like you do riding a bicycle or riding a horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.80,0:40:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And some people are just no good at horses and, therefore, give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.50,0:40:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.50,0:40:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to put a cautionary note that it's not written in stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.38,0:40:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, in writing the book, we did something like 14 or 15 manuscript revisions and thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.07,0:40:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of faxes back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.51,0:40:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it has to be put in a different form than it has to go in some kind of a file on
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.50,0:40:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a computer thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.26,0:40:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it has to be put in a different form so that the printer, you can't just mail
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.82,0:40:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.82,0:40:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he gives you a whole six pages of how he wants it sent to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.09,0:40:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just want you to understand the downside of trying to get everything perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.50,0:40:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.50,0:40:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.73,0:41:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For serenity, you have to give up being perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.34,0:41:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be fallible.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.17,0:41:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be fallible.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.17,0:41:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.05,0:41:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to make a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.26,0:41:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to commit suicide because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.69,0:41:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.69,0:41:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated level of consciousness, we went up to 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.46,0:41:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,600 is the formal beginning of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.90,0:41:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sat Chit Ananda, a state of bliss, the radiance of God shines forth, and all is still.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.25,0:41:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of attachments and aversions.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.84,0:41:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To that which is linear, then you move beyond the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.84,0:41:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The 500s are of course really the goal of most religions and spiritual people, to get
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.07,0:41:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.30,0:42:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And beyond that, through devotion, to get to joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.48,0:42:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Miraculous begins to happen around 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.73,0:42:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,540 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.76,0:42:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The truly miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.80,0:42:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,540 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.84,0:42:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,540 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.63,0:42:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The truly miraculous begin to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.88,0:42:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They occur spontaneously of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.17,0:42:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've spoken of them in previous lectures as the so-called siddhis, S-I-D-D-H-I-S, classically
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.21,0:42:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,paranormal, supernormal phenomena begin to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.03,0:42:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world of the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.13,0:42:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you go through joy and in the very high 500s you go into ecstasy, a strange state.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.80,0:42:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,540.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.92,0:42:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hard to describe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.76,0:42:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy of the presence of God as one's own creation is overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.71,0:42:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you become tireless.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.46,0:42:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can dance for days nonstop.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.03,0:42:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No food, no water, no physical requirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.25,0:43:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it's not your energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.19,0:43:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not dancing, you are being danced.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.55,0:43:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And any of you who have been into that state of ecstasy know
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.40,0:43:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that the dancing now becomes effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.00,0:43:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the witness of the dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.38,0:43:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no you causing the dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.53,0:43:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The dancing is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.42,0:43:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fantastic experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.21,0:43:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people have had that from dancing?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.17,0:43:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here? Dancing, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.09,0:43:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing you get is, what do you call that where you run all day, every day?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.69,0:43:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Running. What do you call that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.67,0:43:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Running. What do you call that? Running.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.09,0:43:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The sport of running.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.11,0:43:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jogging, jogging, jogging.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.71,0:43:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,People.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.36,0:43:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,People jogging and all of a sudden time stops
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.38,0:43:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the woods becomes transformed and they're being jogged.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.65,0:43:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.76,0:43:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It is a very achievable state.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.30,0:44:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I achieved it at age probably 16, yeah, working in a warehouse
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.84,0:44:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in the tremendous heat at a pecanry.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.26,0:44:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You got an extra nickel everything over 12 hours, 35 cents.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.76,0:44:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And after working something like 14 or 15 hours, I said, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.67,0:44:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot lift another box.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.36,0:44:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.46,0:44:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.55,0:44:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly, the I can't, I broke through my sheer determination, the I can't,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.15,0:44:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and came into a wondrous space.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.65,0:44:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Effortlessly, the boxes lifted themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.05,0:44:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I kept working another, I think I worked about 20 hours nonstop.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.05,0:44:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Effortlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.15,0:44:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the heat didn't bother me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.15,0:44:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So you break through, I call it the Roger Bannister barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.15,0:44:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind has a conviction that it can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.36,0:44:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you refuse the can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.36,0:44:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just right through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.21,0:45:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you enter an infinite silent state of spontaneity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.21,0:45:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is required eventually to reach enlightenment as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.25,0:45:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I mentioned the Roger Bannister effect also applies to states of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.25,0:45:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can't, I can't this, I can't that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.38,0:45:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you break through the I can't and realize that you can,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.38,0:45:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,all the I can'ts in spirituality, if we hold a loaded gun to your head,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.67,0:45:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and give you the option, you're going to forgive that guy or I'll blow your brains out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.67,0:45:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.67,0:45:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't that you can't, it's that you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.67,0:45:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And why won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.67,0:45:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't because the ego gets so much juice from its positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.76,0:45:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So what holds all these levels of consciousness in place then,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.82,0:45:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the ego is thriving off the juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.82,0:45:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of injustice, righteousness, being right, winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.01,0:46:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All those positionalities that we're willing to die for.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.50,0:46:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People are willing to die for all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.50,0:46:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.50,0:46:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't mentioned one that appeals to me yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.44,0:46:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like freedom from your speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.44,0:46:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You get free speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.42,0:46:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so that's about 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.69,0:46:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then these states go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.69,0:46:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, for the first time in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.69,0:46:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you can validate spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.69,0:46:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.69,0:46:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can validate spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.57,0:46:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said that close to 80% of the world's population.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.57,0:46:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, now this is not written in cement.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.57,0:46:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, not written in cement.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.57,0:46:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This means at the time we did this, probably five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.57,0:46:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if it's accurate now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.50,0:47:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's, no, I don't want to know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.50,0:47:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe 79% or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.17,0:47:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Roughly, roughly 80% of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.17,0:47:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That mankind is, that's the mass of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.17,0:47:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And about 15, this few percent, 22%, is above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.17,0:47:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the thing is, the power of these people
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.17,0:47:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalances the negative energy of these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.36,0:47:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The negative energy, we got that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.73,0:47:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,without the emergence of the great avatars over time,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.73,0:47:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that mankind would have destroyed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.73,0:47:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind would have destroyed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.03,0:47:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially, you give him an atomic bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.03,0:47:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's controlled by a glow of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.03,0:47:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the end is in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.03,0:47:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter how soon, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.25,0:47:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The evolution of consciousness, happily,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.25,0:47:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is expanding at a rapid rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.25,0:47:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And Daniel Lyons, who sent this to us, calibrated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.15,0:48:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an engineering student.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.15,0:48:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the levels of consciousness over great eons of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.15,0:48:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll quickly review again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.15,0:48:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And here it is against time,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.15,0:48:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.15,0:48:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it's rocketing up at an extremely rapid rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.15,0:48:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of all mankind right now is 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.15,0:48:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,207. Let's see if it's still at 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.15,0:48:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have sneaked up while we were sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.15,0:48:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.50,0:48:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have permission to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.57,0:48:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it 207?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.73,0:48:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,208?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.73,0:48:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,207, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.86,0:48:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,207.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.46,0:48:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, when we do kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.46,0:48:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.46,0:48:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we really phrase it, mentally or verbally,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.46,0:48:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.46,0:48:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the name of the highest good is merely,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.46,0:48:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,scientifically, you're trying to ascertain what is the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.46,0:48:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have any stake in it one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.46,0:48:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason people get very far off answers
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.46,0:48:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is they're putting a stake
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.46,0:49:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in it, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.46,0:49:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter calibrates it over 900.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.78,0:49:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We get letters like that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.78,0:49:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get over that is to calibrate your neighbor's daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.61,0:49:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what she comes out as.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.21,0:49:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's only her daughter, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.34,0:49:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so here we recapitulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.34,0:49:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I think because there's an enormous spiritual benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.34,0:49:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in realizing, what time is the break anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.34,0:49:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,1150?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.34,0:49:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.34,0:49:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.23,0:49:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So how much time have I got?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.23,0:49:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the people who are familiar with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.13,0:49:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we just want to quickly review.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.13,0:49:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The emergence of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.19,0:49:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the great, the oldest dates of rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.19,0:49:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,rocks, and these numbers are so big,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.19,0:49:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know what they are, quadrillions or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.19,0:49:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Heptamillions.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.19,0:49:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Octamillions.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.19,0:49:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Octamillions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.19,0:49:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There are decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.19,0:49:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they're at the evolution of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.65,0:49:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.65,0:50:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to rise over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.65,0:50:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.67,0:50:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.67,0:50:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows up here as bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.67,0:50:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and then marine invertebrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.67,0:50:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the trilobite, etc., like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.67,0:50:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the spiny fish and the amphibians,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.67,0:50:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it begins to climb to the present time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.67,0:50:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the scale of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.67,0:50:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,how it's rising continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.67,0:50:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.90,0:50:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are on the upside.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.90,0:50:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,People alive today
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.90,0:50:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,then have the benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.90,0:50:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is an upward momentum
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.90,0:50:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.90,0:50:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the chances of reaching enlightenment now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.90,0:50:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are over a thousand times greater
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.90,0:50:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,than any time in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.51,0:50:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,due to consciousness research,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.51,0:50:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,due to the advance of the level of consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.51,0:50:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you skip guilt about sin, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.51,0:50:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do it in 20, 30 weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.51,0:51:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.51,0:51:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.51,0:51:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it saves you plenty of lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.42,0:51:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How long does it take to become enlightened?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.42,0:51:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One second,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.42,0:51:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,except that it takes you most of a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.42,0:51:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to that second.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.90,0:51:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so I think this is,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.90,0:51:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, as a psychiatrist, psychoanalyst,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.90,0:51:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,psychologist, physician, and researcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.09,0:51:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as a spiritual committed person myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.21,0:51:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I consider this very important, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.11,0:51:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because here you have the emergence of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.11,0:51:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see its origin is in the animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.11,0:51:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.11,0:51:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.11,0:51:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's animal, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.40,0:51:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy isn't evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.40,0:51:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A shark isn't evil, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.40,0:51:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.15,0:51:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.17,0:52:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He just is being what he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.17,0:52:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.84,0:52:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Dolphins are not evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.09,0:52:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Polar bears are not evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.09,0:52:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Bears are not evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.40,0:52:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.82,0:52:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see any evil there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.82,0:52:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I see an animal being an animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.82,0:52:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So under 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.53,0:52:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the animals being an animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.53,0:52:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it lives at the cost of the life of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.59,0:52:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Predation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.75,0:52:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are characterized by predation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.75,0:52:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.75,0:52:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.75,0:52:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you see a major transformation,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.75,0:52:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,not only in mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.75,0:52:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the animal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.75,0:52:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.75,0:52:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the emergence
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.65,0:52:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the herbivore,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.65,0:52:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the grazer.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.65,0:52:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These are rapacious killers.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.67,0:52:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These just bunch their grass
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.67,0:52:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and fertilize it all at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.05,0:53:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who goes in one end,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.40,0:53:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,fertilizer out the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.40,0:53:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're even-steven, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.82,0:53:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They fertilize the grass while they eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.03,0:53:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.03,0:53:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why we have dairy cows.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.03,0:53:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.03,0:53:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then we get up to the higher animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.03,0:53:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the dogs and the cats
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.94,0:53:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the gorillas and Coco.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.13,0:53:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's see what Coco calibrates on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.67,0:53:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.38,0:53:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If I think of Coco and Coco as an identity,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.38,0:53:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco calibrates over 400, 405, 406.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.42,0:53:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.51,0:53:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If I think of Coco as gorilla,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.01,0:53:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco calibrates over 250, 260.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.01,0:53:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.13,0:53:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.03,0:53:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a discrepancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.03,0:53:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In one place,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.03,0:53:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I said Coco calibrated 250
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.03,0:53:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and another 405.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.03,0:53:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when I said 250,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.03,0:53:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.03,0:54:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I got 405,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.03,0:54:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking specifically Coco.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.61,0:54:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When we got 250,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.61,0:54:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was holding a picture of a gorilla
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.61,0:54:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wasn't making it Coco.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.61,0:54:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.61,0:54:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we hear about these discrepancies
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.61,0:54:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I feel obligated to explain them
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.61,0:54:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and research them myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.61,0:54:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've learned a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.51,0:54:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,about the discrepancies.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.51,0:54:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.51,0:54:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So Coco, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.51,0:54:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,gorillas are somewhere else on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.51,0:54:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget where.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.51,0:54:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you're safer with a gorilla
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.51,0:54:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,than you are with most people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.51,0:54:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where the gorilla is.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.51,0:54:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the gorilla?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.26,0:54:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.26,0:54:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So gorillas, depending on the gorilla,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.26,0:54:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's different kinds of gorillas,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.26,0:54:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there's highland and lowland, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.26,0:54:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.26,0:54:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guess the bees,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.26,0:54:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, scientific research,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.26,0:54:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.15,0:54:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Highland and one country
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.15,0:54:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,versus the lowland
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.15,0:54:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's a difference
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.15,0:54:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,between the highland gorillas
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.15,0:54:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the lowland gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.15,0:54:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.15,0:54:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whether Coco represents Coco.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.96,0:55:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.96,0:55:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.96,0:55:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,she's sending me messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.03,0:55:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I get your message.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.96,0:55:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to insult Coco.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.96,0:55:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.96,0:55:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.96,0:55:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, scientific research,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.96,0:55:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,then we'd have to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.86,0:55:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco is a highland or a lowland.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.86,0:55:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And Coco at what age, et cetera, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.86,0:55:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But we want to get a gist of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.86,0:55:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The gist of it is that these are rapacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.86,0:55:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,These are benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.86,0:55:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the corollary with human life is exact.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.86,0:55:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The correlation is 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.86,0:55:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is certainly very something
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.86,0:55:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we can learn from.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.94,0:55:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a great parrot
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.94,0:55:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we're playing with at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.94,0:55:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.84,0:55:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your latest thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.05,0:55:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.05,0:55:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.05,0:55:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.05,0:56:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.92,0:56:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She's far right conservative.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.92,0:56:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.94,0:56:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you want an apple,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.94,0:56:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,get your own, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.94,0:56:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we know the cat's fur
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.94,0:56:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dog's wanging tail
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.94,0:56:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is unique at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.94,0:56:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.94,0:56:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the animal kingdom, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.94,0:56:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is corollary,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.94,0:56:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,correlated with the human.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.94,0:56:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego, the development of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.94,0:56:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that we just saw that,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.94,0:56:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.94,0:56:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.59,0:56:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.59,0:56:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.59,0:56:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great books of the western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.59,0:56:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to cover those things
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.61,0:56:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that came up because of the errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.61,0:56:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to explain them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.71,0:56:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The limitations of kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.78,0:56:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside is it gives you access
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.78,0:56:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to information never before available
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.78,0:56:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to anyone anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.67,0:57:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And for which you have respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.44,0:57:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.61,0:57:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.61,0:57:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.61,0:57:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And again,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.61,0:57:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because people have requested
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.61,0:57:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll repeat something
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.61,0:57:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we've said in previous lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.61,0:57:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it all come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.61,0:57:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The scale is,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.61,0:57:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is a scale aligned with
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.11,0:57:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of something
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.11,0:57:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.11,0:57:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.23,0:57:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, there is no variation
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.71,0:57:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in the absolute because
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.71,0:57:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the omnipotence of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.71,0:57:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the omnipotence, the omnipresence,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.71,0:57:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is the scale against which
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.92,0:57:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we're calibrating truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.92,0:57:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Roughly equivalent to,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.13,0:57:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say operationally,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.13,0:57:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to an electromagnetic,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.13,0:57:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the old speakers where the,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.94,0:57:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call the speakers?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.94,0:57:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Electro something speakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.94,0:58:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll come to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.15,0:58:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So electrostatic, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.15,0:58:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Electrostatic speakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.15,0:58:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the greater the charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.15,0:58:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you remember how
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.15,0:58:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the electrostatic speaker works,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.15,0:58:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is the greater the membrane,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.15,0:58:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater the electrons
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.15,0:58:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,on this membrane,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.15,0:58:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they can't touch the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.15,0:58:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater the number
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.15,0:58:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of protons will.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.15,0:58:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the response is always exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.15,0:58:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,consequent and aligned
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.28,0:58:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the stimulus.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.19,0:58:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness then.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.44,0:58:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So with kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.44,0:58:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what you get is that the stimulus
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.44,0:58:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you present, coco,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.44,0:58:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,then brings up a response.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.44,0:58:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that response is the equivalent
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.44,0:58:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and we call that 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.96,0:58:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.05,0:58:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has no beginning and no ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.05,0:58:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It is outside of time
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.76,0:58:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and within it everything
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.11,0:58:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is recorded forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.01,0:59:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Every hair on your head is numbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.36,0:59:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Numbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.59,0:59:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They get fewer.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.13,0:59:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say it's not saying numbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.13,0:59:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Count it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.13,0:59:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that is done
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.63,0:59:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is recorded in the infinite field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.63,0:59:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.63,0:59:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.09,0:59:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.09,0:59:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.51,0:59:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone is accountable
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.51,0:59:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for their actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.51,0:59:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically responsible for their actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.51,0:59:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Culpability
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.23,0:59:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,changes depending on the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.23,0:59:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Accountability does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.23,0:59:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Culpability is, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.75,0:59:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the concept that one's degree
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.75,0:59:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowledge or awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.75,0:59:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or ignorance at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.75,0:59:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be taken into consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.07,0:59:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At a certain level, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.80,1:00:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,all men are innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.80,1:00:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All men are innocent
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.15,1:00:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.57,1:00:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that as Socrates said,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.69,1:00:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,all men choose,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.59,1:00:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not only the good,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.78,1:00:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they choose what their experiencer pro
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.78,1:00:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks is the best option,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.78,1:00:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,believes is the best option
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.78,1:00:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to take at any given moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.78,1:00:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So intrinsically the mind is innocent
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.78,1:00:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've compared it many times
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.78,1:00:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to the computer,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.94,1:00:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the hardware of the computer
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.98,1:00:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.98,1:00:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is not able to reach truth on its own
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.98,1:00:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because like a hardware of a computer
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.98,1:00:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it will play any kind of program
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.98,1:00:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you put into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.17,1:00:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer has no,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.17,1:00:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,its hardware has no means
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.17,1:00:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of evaluating the value
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.32,1:00:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,or much less the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.32,1:00:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of any program.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.32,1:00:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.32,1:00:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,can be programmed very easily.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.32,1:00:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's programmed, in fact, automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.32,1:01:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.32,1:01:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsically, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.13,1:01:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego is set up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.13,1:01:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the mind is unable
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.13,1:01:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.13,1:01:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts res interna from res externa.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.13,1:01:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The world as we see it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.48,1:01:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.48,1:01:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a bridge
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.73,1:01:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and no way to really cross it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.73,1:01:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,until recently.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.82,1:01:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.82,1:01:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with consciousness research
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.88,1:01:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the first time we've been able
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.88,1:01:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to cross the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.88,1:01:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we see it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.88,1:01:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and what does it calibrate out as?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.88,1:01:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you see if there's a disparity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.88,1:01:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get why perception saw it that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.88,1:01:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you pick up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.88,1:01:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is a positionality within yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.88,1:01:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's some gain
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.88,1:01:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're getting out of seeing it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.88,1:01:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you were seeing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.94,1:01:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting some kind of gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.46,1:02:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.46,1:02:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is relatively immune.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.46,1:02:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't tell truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.46,1:02:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is the great tragedy
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.46,1:02:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.46,1:02:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For that reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.46,1:02:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great avatars appeared over time
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.46,1:02:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were the only real avenues
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.36,1:02:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.36,1:02:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Real avenues of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.36,1:02:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,without which man would have exterminated himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.36,1:02:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the limitations.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.78,1:02:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And so,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.78,1:02:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,how do things come about?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.78,1:02:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritually? Karma?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.78,1:02:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Christian world doesn't think
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.78,1:02:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,they believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.78,1:02:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.78,1:02:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All Christians believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.78,1:02:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They just don't call it karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.78,1:02:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Heaven or hell, where the soul goes after death,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.78,1:02:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that's called karma, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.71,1:02:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason to avoid sin
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.71,1:02:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is you want to avoid the lower regions
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.71,1:02:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.59,1:02:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't get to vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.63,1:03:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so to transcend the limitations, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.48,1:03:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.48,1:03:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so consciousness research,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.48,1:03:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,one of its benefits is it gave us a way
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.48,1:03:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to access information not otherwise available.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.48,1:03:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.48,1:03:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a radiance of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.48,1:03:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is comparable to a giant electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.38,1:03:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual dimension is comparable.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.51,1:03:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.51,1:03:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of God is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.51,1:03:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so by our choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.51,1:03:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by our own options of choice, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.51,1:03:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we determine, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.51,1:03:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,our spiritual charge.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.51,1:03:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, you might picture
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.51,1:03:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're a little piece of metal fragment.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.51,1:03:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And every choice you make
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.53,1:03:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,influences your polarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.53,1:03:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And every choice you make
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.53,1:03:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,influences your polarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.61,1:03:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, where you are
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.61,1:03:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in the infinite field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.61,1:04:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is the automatic consequence of choices,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.61,1:04:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.61,1:04:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the choices that you've made throughout time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.69,1:04:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that which you have chosen.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.69,1:04:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And within an infinite field of power,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.69,1:04:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonally,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.98,1:04:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you are drawn and pulled to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.98,1:04:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that area of the electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.98,1:04:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you don't need an arbitrary,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.98,1:04:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,judgmental God
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.98,1:04:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.13,1:04:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the justice of God
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.13,1:04:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is absolutely perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.13,1:04:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing happens and nobody goes
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.50,1:04:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,any place other than by their own choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.53,1:04:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody paddling the canoe but us.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.53,1:04:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't blame it on God.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.53,1:04:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the anthropomorphic God
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.53,1:04:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is angry and jealous and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.53,1:04:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of sort of primitivism.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.53,1:04:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Primitive man saw volcanoes and floods and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.65,1:05:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,postulated angry gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.23,1:05:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they sacrificed maidens and etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.23,1:05:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to satisfy the angry gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.30,1:05:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Maidens were always the favorite.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.30,1:05:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Maidens...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.51,1:05:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Innocent maidens were the favorite, for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.51,1:05:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A grizzly little guy doesn't seem to be much of a sacrifice, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.51,1:05:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sexism goes way back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.05,1:05:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Only virgin maidens.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.05,1:05:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.71,1:05:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to define the relationship of context and...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.82,1:05:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,See, content and context.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.82,1:05:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Content is linear, definable, calculable.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.92,1:05:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of science and mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.92,1:05:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The field is the overall context.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.92,1:05:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And as for spiritual evolution, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.92,1:05:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always recommended the contemplative lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.92,1:05:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you align with the field
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.07,1:05:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.07,1:06:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you walk about in a style
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.00,1:06:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and state of greater serenity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.05,1:06:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're upset at everything that happens on the television,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.05,1:06:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not going to get to sleep, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.05,1:06:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you see is the panorama of the cacophony
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.05,1:06:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of political maneuvering and game playing
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.05,1:06:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because everybody wants power, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.05,1:06:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you just assume, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.05,1:06:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see it's not affecting your serenity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.05,1:06:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's like a game.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.21,1:06:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you see it as a game,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.11,1:06:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,your serenity remains the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.11,1:06:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take it seriously,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.11,1:06:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be upset all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.11,1:06:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here takes politics seriously?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.15,1:06:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can't take it seriously
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.15,1:06:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because everybody says what they think
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.15,1:06:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,will appeal to their own followers.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.15,1:07:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't have anything to do with truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.51,1:07:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with winning.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.51,1:07:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Politicians are not here for your good, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.51,1:07:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not their purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.40,1:07:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Your good gets them elected.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.40,1:07:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, therefore, you're good.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.34,1:07:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No politician is aligned with truth
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.34,1:07:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for the good karma of society.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.34,1:07:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, because he couldn't be able to sleep at night.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.55,1:07:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.21,1:07:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the functions of mind, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.21,1:07:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's various energy fields
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.21,1:07:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that are controlled by what are called the tractor fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.21,1:07:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In that which seems scattered,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.51,1:07:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there is an overall organizing principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.51,1:07:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called an attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.51,1:07:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Attractor field comes from nonlinear dynamics.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.51,1:07:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That which appears to be sporadic,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.51,1:07:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear, unpredictable,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.51,1:07:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is off the chart,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.51,1:08:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,being controlled by a higher field of context.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.51,1:08:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we calibrate,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.57,1:08:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we find that there's two levels to mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.57,1:08:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's lower mind and higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.82,1:08:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower mind is the thinkingness of people below time.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.82,1:08:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a 200, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.82,1:08:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And they go in for, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.31,1:08:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,sympathy instead of empathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.38,1:08:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Big difference between sympathy and empathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.50,1:08:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sympathy calibrates low.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.50,1:08:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Empathy calibrates high.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.60,1:08:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to be sensitive to where other people are
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.60,1:08:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore makes you a greater gift to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.68,1:08:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sympathy gets to be maudlin
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.59,1:08:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and gets to be, it's a way of milking the situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.59,1:08:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the crybaby society
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.59,1:08:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on always milking the world for some sympathy
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.59,1:09:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for something that happened to you in your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.59,1:09:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,some circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.59,1:09:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that won't do it, you can always go back to ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.59,1:09:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always ancestors that have been screwed over.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.47,1:09:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If you run out of victim rolls,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.68,1:09:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I can, anybody short a victim roll,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.68,1:09:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll manufacture you a couple of them right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.59,1:09:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,White males right now are the ultra-victim of our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.35,1:09:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, all white males have to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.35,1:09:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's comical.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.15,1:09:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the lower mind then is motivated more by animal kinds of wants
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.18,1:09:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as they are elaborated by the prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.18,1:09:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened is we watched the evolution of consciousness over time
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.18,1:09:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then emerges the hominids.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.07,1:09:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think hominids are on there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.23,1:09:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No, hominids aren't on that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.81,1:09:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the hominids began about, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.81,1:10:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the last guess I heard was three million years ago with Lucy,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.81,1:10:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which I don't think is fair either.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.01,1:10:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have been George, you know, if they got to be Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.47,1:10:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Lucy was the first hominid.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.47,1:10:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And Lucy we calibrated the other day.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.80,1:10:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what Lucy was at, around 65 or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.51,1:10:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, then we have the hominids appearing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.51,1:10:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the Neanderthal man, Homo erectus, about 85.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.40,1:10:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Homo erectus, I-delta, about 60,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.40,1:10:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.47,1:10:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,evolving through the hominids.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.47,1:10:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the hominids.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.50,1:10:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, region 205, where it is today.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.50,1:10:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.50,1:10:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I went over that slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.50,1:10:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So on its way, no, we'll go back to the previous one.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.85,1:10:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,On its way, then, to erudition, which is in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.07,1:11:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it goes through lower mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.07,1:11:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,where it tends to be naive, gullible, and impressionable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.07,1:11:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the world of rhetoric, persuasion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.07,1:11:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare they? How can we do so-and-so?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.07,1:11:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lot of drama and theater, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.07,1:11:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And people then, they're coming mainly from emotion,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.07,1:11:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and fall for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.97,1:11:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are coming from the intellect and logic
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.97,1:11:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,are coming from a higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.97,1:11:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And what sells over here doesn't sell over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.97,1:11:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, this sounds awful dry and unappealing
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.97,1:11:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to people over here who are interested in
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.97,1:11:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a cheering squad and emotion and the band playing, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.97,1:11:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotional band playing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.42,1:11:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to the great books of the Western world?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.42,1:11:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you do something with them?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.56,1:11:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She did something with the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.96,1:12:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw how, you know, through the emergence of the hominid,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.18,1:12:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the emergence of intelligence, calibrated levels constantly rising,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.18,1:12:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and probably the greatest, the height of human civilization.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.18,1:12:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,To my mind, the height of human civilization was around 350 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.18,1:12:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's frankly slowly going downhill soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.18,1:12:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not too optimistic of you, is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.18,1:12:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.27,1:12:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The roots, the paradigm for all of Western civilization
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.31,1:12:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,was set around in the 5th century B.C.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.31,1:12:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Plato and Socrates, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.40,1:12:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly, nothing has come out since then,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.40,1:12:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectually, that calibrates higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.40,1:12:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.40,1:12:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of things have come out that are lower,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.40,1:12:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but nothing has come out higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.40,1:12:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the rules of logic,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.47,1:13:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the axiom categories, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.47,1:13:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,were discovered, and they're not going to change over time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.47,1:13:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if somebody, if you quote Socrates,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.47,1:13:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,some people say, well, that's so old-fashioned, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.47,1:13:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, other truths were discovered at that time,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.93,1:13:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly, it hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.93,1:13:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right, we calibrated the great books of the Western world,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.93,1:13:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and that in itself is a really wonderful exercise.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.93,1:13:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the great books are still available.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.84,1:13:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's recommended you study them over a ten-year period.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.84,1:13:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You divide this up into ten,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.84,1:13:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and each year you spend,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.84,1:13:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, just reading, familiarize yourself with three or four writers,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.84,1:13:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.84,1:13:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you achieve what's really the ultimate goal
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.84,1:13:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of the liberal education,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.84,1:13:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the establishment of the comprehension of Western society
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.84,1:13:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and its intellectual basis.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.84,1:13:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A great deal, just studying the great books
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.07,1:14:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Western world makes a profound difference
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.07,1:14:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in how you see and understand the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.07,1:14:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have Darwin at 450, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.30,1:14:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's, of course, right in the middle of it right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.71,1:14:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And Copernicus at 455.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.71,1:14:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the great scientists.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.71,1:14:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Very amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.71,1:14:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle at close to 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.71,1:14:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And Socrates is not on here,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.71,1:14:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because he never wrote anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.89,1:14:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, somebody inquired,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.80,1:14:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and they discovered information about Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.80,1:14:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, the encyclopedia,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.80,1:14:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which would answer the question,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.69,1:14:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,where is it written about Socrates?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.69,1:14:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, that was written by Plato.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.69,1:14:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin reading Plato's Phaedus, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.69,1:14:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and Republic, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.69,1:14:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand what Socrates said.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.69,1:14:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so these things are very significant
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.69,1:15:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're out of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.10,1:15:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the whole world that we call civilization,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.10,1:15:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,society being decent, rational, and reasonable,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.10,1:15:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is really the product of the intellects
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.27,1:15:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of these people over time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.88,1:15:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate collectively around 450, 455.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.88,1:15:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to give specifics anymore,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.88,1:15:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because somebody's going to send me an email,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.88,1:15:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said 455.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.88,1:15:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.77,1:15:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all numbers will be roundabout.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.77,1:15:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Roundabout, the more, the mid-400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.77,1:15:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you have intellectual erudition.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.80,1:15:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Roundabout, and here, roundabout.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.67,1:15:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you do see people, Descartes at 490,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.67,1:15:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Freud at 499,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.67,1:15:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton at 499,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.56,1:15:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,develop the differential calculus.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.56,1:15:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the great scientific minds,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.56,1:16:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Galileo, Galen, Hegel.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.56,1:16:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel's principle, I always mention,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.56,1:16:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because he had a principle of the absolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.56,1:16:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and that principle of the absolute
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.56,1:16:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is the whole basis of kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.56,1:16:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you have the father of medicine.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.56,1:16:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you really have the great and celebrated minds of history
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.56,1:16:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who had a profound and positive impact on mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.56,1:16:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With the exception of this ringer in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.56,1:16:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Marxian dialectic materialism calibrates to 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.68,1:16:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the fallout of calibrated level 130
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.85,1:16:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is about 100 million lives in my lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.85,1:16:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,all of Marxism,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.85,1:16:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course the thousands of millions of deaths
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.85,1:16:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that have come through.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.85,1:16:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the problem with Marxism?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.94,1:16:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dualistic projection of the concept
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.85,1:17:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.85,1:17:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the downside of moral relativism as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.42,1:17:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It constantly sees a perpetrator and a victim,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.42,1:17:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and that divides people into warring factions.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.42,1:17:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you take Marx out of this,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.42,1:17:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they all calibrate, this calibrates around 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.42,1:17:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take out Marx,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.42,1:17:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,collectively they calibrate around 465.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.42,1:17:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore spiritual error
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.42,1:17:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is a serious matter, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.44,1:17:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And Socrates said that one of his main purposes
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.64,1:17:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,was to destroy the gods of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.64,1:17:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroy the gods of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.67,1:17:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So Socrates being my brother,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.67,1:17:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I joined with him and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.67,1:17:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,here you have at 130 one of the gods of falsity.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.40,1:18:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mayo's Little Red Book.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.47,1:18:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How many millions? 30 million died just of starvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.47,1:18:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Just of starvation, forget war.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.65,1:18:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Cold War.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.65,1:18:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of falsehood is very serious, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.65,1:18:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking about in my lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.94,1:18:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,at least 100 million people.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.94,1:18:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At least 100 million people have gone to their death
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.27,1:18:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because of just this error here.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.27,1:18:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Just that error.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.13,1:18:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore we don't hate negativity,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.73,1:18:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but I certainly respect it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.73,1:18:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect that which is spoken in error,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.73,1:18:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,especially if it's spoken with great fervor
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.73,1:18:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and rhetorical skill.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.73,1:18:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's instantly the Achilles heel
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.96,1:18:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that can bring down our society as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.96,1:18:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And in our own research we said
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.43,1:19:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the combination of totalitarian, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.84,1:19:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,theological totalitarianism on one side
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.84,1:19:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and moral relativism on the other side,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.89,1:19:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by the sheer process of iteration,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.06,1:19:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,where one, the apologist, opens the door to the other,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.76,1:19:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,does have the capacity to destroy our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.89,1:19:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It does have the capacity to destroy our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.89,1:19:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,By iteration.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.89,1:19:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The constant introduction of falsehood in the media,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.81,1:19:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the newspapers, the commentators,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.21,1:19:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and most dangerously at the university level,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.88,1:19:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,academically,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.93,1:19:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to impair the reality testing of the student then,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.93,1:19:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by aligning it with falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.93,1:19:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is then the problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.42,1:19:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How to maintain serenity in the midst of all this is simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.73,1:20:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You just turn it over to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.64,1:20:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose, therefore, to not be serene about it means
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.43,1:20:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that you know more about the purpose of human life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.43,1:20:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,than divinity does.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.43,1:20:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of human life does not seem to be
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.06,1:20:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially, subjectively, emotionally serenity at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.06,1:20:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.93,1:20:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because serenity as a way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.93,1:20:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't really happen, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.93,1:20:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,until you get up into the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.02,1:20:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So serenity is really the world of maybe 3 or 4% of the people in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.31,1:20:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, they choose serenity above the payoff of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.52,1:20:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we get back, I just want to recapitulate briefly.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.52,1:20:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What I call the experiencer edge of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.52,1:21:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It feeds off something out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.52,1:21:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's constantly probing and looking.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.52,1:21:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It loves conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.43,1:21:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It loves excitement.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.43,1:21:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It loves war and terrorism and all these wonderful things.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.43,1:21:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It lives off that juice.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.43,1:21:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, serenity seems to the ego like suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.64,1:21:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing the ego wants,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.64,1:21:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it feeds off the animal juice of excitement.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.64,1:21:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing it wants is serenity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.64,1:21:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, what brings about this serenity
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.64,1:21:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is at consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.55,1:21:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you get a transformation of brain physiology
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.55,1:21:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because you have the introduction of a new energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.55,1:21:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.55,1:21:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,classically called kundalini energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.55,1:21:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which completely changes and alters your brain function.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.55,1:21:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person above 200 and the person below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.55,1:21:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are even on the animal level different,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.55,1:21:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that the brain of this one is working different
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.55,1:22:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,than the brain of the other one.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.55,1:22:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So after the break,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.44,1:22:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we have that slide coming up.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.44,1:22:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't we, brain physiology?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.44,1:22:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.77,1:22:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I apologize to those who have heard this before,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.77,1:22:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,except each time it's different
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.77,1:22:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're a different person.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.77,1:22:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you heard it before,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.77,1:22:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you're different than you were when you heard it,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.77,1:22:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or I missed my point.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.77,1:22:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have kept my own piece.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.77,1:22:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopefully, to have heard it,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.85,1:22:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're different than you were before you heard it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.85,1:22:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, you're not the same people
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.85,1:22:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,who heard this before.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.06,1:22:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're different people.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.46,1:22:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And for you, it's the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.46,1:22:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take a break till what time?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.56,1:22:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take a break till what time?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.43,1:22:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, 53 and 59.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.43,1:22:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen minutes?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.69,1:23:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'all students,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.78,1:23:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we will commence again
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.78,1:23:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,from the middle.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.23,1:23:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We start from the ending,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.23,1:23:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,then we recommence at the middle.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.85,1:23:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to cover the didactic material,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.48,1:23:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, for multiple reasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.48,1:23:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, learning is facilitated by repetition.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.64,1:23:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And at first, what may sound amazing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.64,1:23:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or even challenging,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.64,1:23:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes, so what?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.64,1:23:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You become...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.64,1:23:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you learn by familiarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.64,1:23:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one way that's linear,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.64,1:23:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,sequential, logical.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.68,1:23:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other is just you get the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.68,1:23:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,by familiarity, you know, familiarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.68,1:23:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.68,1:23:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, you just accept the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.57,1:23:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's the way it is, so.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.68,1:23:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.68,1:23:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As time goes on,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.02,1:23:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to reduce the amount of didactic time,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.02,1:24:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,spend more time on spontaneous conversation and interaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.02,1:24:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll start that today.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.09,1:24:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico's not going to be here,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.09,1:24:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so we'll have a little more time for questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.81,1:24:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, you know, in other words, time-wise,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.48,1:24:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's absent today.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.48,1:24:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But progressively, we'll spend more time
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.18,1:24:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with spontaneous interaction with the audience, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.18,1:24:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My favorite style, really,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.18,1:24:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is to just wander through the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.18,1:24:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and greet people and they come up with
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.18,1:24:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever they come up with.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.18,1:24:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that makes it more alive
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.18,1:24:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and, you know, experiential.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.18,1:24:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But we all need this kind of background.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.47,1:24:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And this background is information
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.47,1:24:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,never really before been accessible.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.47,1:24:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And it allows us to understand the human life,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.38,1:24:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,from a different level,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.38,1:24:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which supports compassion.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.38,1:25:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody knows that the ultimate spiritual state
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.43,1:25:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they would like to reach,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.43,1:25:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that of the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.43,1:25:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which is compassion for all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.43,1:25:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But that can't be an artificiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.47,1:25:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think I'll be compassionate.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.47,1:25:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Compassion is the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.47,1:25:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.47,1:25:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you comprehend the limitation
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.47,1:25:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of human evolution,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.47,1:25:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the limitations intrinsic,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.47,1:25:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,built into the computer,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.47,1:25:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,software problem of the human mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.47,1:25:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you become compassionate for human error.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.69,1:25:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And you accept human fallibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.69,1:25:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You accept human fallibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.98,1:25:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And become compassionate.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.98,1:25:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, once you become compassionate for others,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.98,1:25:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you also become more compassionate towards yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.98,1:25:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And stop attacking yourself with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.98,1:25:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All humans are fallible.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.02,1:25:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All fallible. All fallible.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.11,1:25:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is set in stone forever, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.11,1:25:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all fallible.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.18,1:26:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we take responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.39,1:26:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,merely to correct our mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.39,1:26:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it isn't that you make a mistake,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.39,1:26:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it's that you take the responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.39,1:26:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to correct it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.85,1:26:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If I put a dish in the wrong place,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.85,1:26:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to take it out and put it where it belongs.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.85,1:26:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I joke with her all the time about those things, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.47,1:26:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But acceptance of fallibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.73,1:26:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the limitations of the human mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.64,1:26:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then allows for a certain serenity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.98,1:26:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates' dictum, which I quote constantly,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.98,1:26:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because once you've accepted it,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.98,1:26:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it solves a multitude of problems,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.98,1:26:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is that all men choose only what they perceive to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.98,1:26:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All men are intrinsically innocent by virtue of the fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.02,1:26:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They always choose what appears to be the best option at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.18,1:26:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is another way of explaining
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.97,1:27:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the same thing that I try to explain
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.97,1:27:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,using the analogy of the computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.97,1:27:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That the human mind cannot differentiate truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.14,1:27:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has no guards at the gate
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.14,1:27:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to filter in the truth of what it's being programmed with.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.14,1:27:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, the human mind is programmed
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.19,1:27:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so rapidly that it's happened before you realize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.19,1:27:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.27,1:27:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,About the time you realize you've been programmed,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.27,1:27:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.57,1:27:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm programming you right now
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.89,1:27:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to make you aware that the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.93,1:27:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,has a propensity to being quickly programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.93,1:27:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.68,1:27:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Innocently, because that's the way it's built.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.69,1:27:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As noted by Descartes,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.69,1:27:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the world you think you see
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.69,1:27:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world the way it is
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.69,1:27:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are quite disparate.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.69,1:28:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And very frequently they have no relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.69,1:28:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to each other at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.61,1:28:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings about a certain intrinsic humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.61,1:28:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So like compassion,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.46,1:28:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,humility automatically ensues
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.46,1:28:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,from the comprehension and acceptance
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.46,1:28:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the limitations of the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.61,1:28:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only your own, but human mind over history.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.61,1:28:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Over all of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.61,1:28:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That fallacy has reigned for...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.71,1:28:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In human history, you realize,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.81,1:28:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,peace has prevailed 93...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.81,1:28:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace has prevailed 7% of the time
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.71,1:28:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in human history.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.71,1:28:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And war has prevailed 93% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.71,1:28:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're against war,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.27,1:28:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you're against normality, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.27,1:28:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Man loves to be at war.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.27,1:28:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The glory of war.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.27,1:28:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The righteousness of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.27,1:29:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.89,1:29:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, if this is a world
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.14,1:29:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of great karmic opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.14,1:29:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,war is one of the greatest karmic opportunities
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.14,1:29:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that mankind has.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.14,1:29:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,To undo negative karma
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.05,1:29:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and to cross over the line
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.05,1:29:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of 200 into integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.05,1:29:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the valor of the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.14,1:29:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the warrior, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.30,1:29:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll celebrate that
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.30,1:29:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,at one of these coming lectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.30,1:29:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna have bagpipes.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.30,1:29:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.30,1:29:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody hate bagpipes?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.71,1:29:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people hate them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.71,1:29:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm giving forewarning
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.77,1:29:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that without being previously announced,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.18,1:29:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you may be hit by bagpipes
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.18,1:29:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,during any lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.07,1:29:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Bagpipes calibrate about 510.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.07,1:29:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you understand
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.27,1:29:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of bagpipes,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.27,1:29:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll understand
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.27,1:29:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a different dimension of war
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.27,1:29:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that you don't understand before.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.27,1:29:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because without the energy of bagpipes,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.27,1:30:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't really comprehend it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.36,1:30:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What war has always been about,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.36,1:30:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what the stereotype,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.36,1:30:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what the archetype of the warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.36,1:30:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is all about.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.36,1:30:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And its karmic upside
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.36,1:30:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and its karmic downside, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.28,1:30:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, you remember Jesus Christ said
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.47,1:30:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he did not come with a sword of peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.47,1:30:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but a sword of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.47,1:30:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't he say that?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.57,1:30:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Any Christians here?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.57,1:30:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, anybody?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.93,1:30:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Five out of six Americans are Christian.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.93,1:30:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.98,1:30:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.98,1:30:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to study scripture.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.98,1:30:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's old-fashioned.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.98,1:30:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, but he did say
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.98,1:30:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn't bring a sword of peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.56,1:30:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,he brought the sword of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.47,1:30:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm seeing contentious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.47,1:30:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It can seem contentious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.47,1:30:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not contentious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.47,1:30:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a challenge
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.47,1:30:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to the ego's belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.07,1:30:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.07,1:31:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to point out
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.07,1:31:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that because of animal nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.07,1:31:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,80% of the people on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.07,1:31:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,are dominated
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.07,1:31:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in such a way
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.07,1:31:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that their brain processes
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.07,1:31:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,things differently
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.07,1:31:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,than other people's brains.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.84,1:31:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.84,1:31:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the brain processes
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.84,1:31:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,left brain style animal nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.84,1:31:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,ruled by instincts, ruled by emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.84,1:31:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why reason does not prevail,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.84,1:31:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because the emotion here kicks in.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.84,1:31:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The information is very slow
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.84,1:31:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,through the prefrontal cortex,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.84,1:31:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,very rapid to the emotional center,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.84,1:31:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so people react emotionally
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.84,1:31:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with their solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.84,1:31:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So rhetoric is aimed not at your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.84,1:31:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Rhetoric is aimed at your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.84,1:31:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.34,1:31:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Your emotional state
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.34,1:31:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is aimed at lower mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.38,1:31:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the emergence of homo sapiens,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.38,1:32:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.38,1:32:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened was that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.38,1:32:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the prefrontal cortex was plastered
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.38,1:32:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,onto the old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.85,1:32:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't remove the old animal brain
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.85,1:32:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and replace it with a prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.85,1:32:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They plastered it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.85,1:32:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,onto the old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.85,1:32:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you've got a thinking animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.85,1:32:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So the animal himself
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.38,1:32:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,could be quite dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.38,1:32:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you add thinkingness to him,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.38,1:32:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got modern man,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.38,1:32:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,who is extremely dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.38,1:32:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.38,1:32:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,he should really be put on a different planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.38,1:32:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.38,1:32:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that's my view of it. Sorry, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.42,1:32:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, God says there's got to be
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.42,1:32:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,maximum opportunity
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.42,1:32:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for all to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.42,1:32:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So this world is the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.42,1:32:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.42,1:32:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the Buddha said,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.42,1:32:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,great fortune is it to be born a human,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.42,1:32:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because you were born in a realm
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.31,1:33:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with maximum karmic opportunity
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.31,1:33:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to undo your negative karma
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.31,1:33:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and to gain positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.31,1:33:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Through evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.72,1:33:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritual energy
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.72,1:33:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,finally emerges,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.72,1:33:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and through your own commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.94,1:33:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and your own choices,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.94,1:33:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you move into an energy field above 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.94,1:33:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and dramatic change takes place
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.94,1:33:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in your brain function.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.94,1:33:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Very dramatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.88,1:33:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The people below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.88,1:33:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,are not the same as you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.88,1:33:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.18,1:33:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They are different.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.18,1:33:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have the same vision
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.42,1:33:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will see one way,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.42,1:33:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they will see another way,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.42,1:33:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because their brain processes it differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.42,1:33:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't that they're wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.42,1:33:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or evil or something,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.42,1:33:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just that they get it differently
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.51,1:33:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,than you get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.85,1:33:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They get it differently than you get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.85,1:33:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So this brain here now,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.85,1:33:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the fast-track is through
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.85,1:33:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a comprehension
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.85,1:34:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,emotion is delayed,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.85,1:34:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and at consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.32,1:34:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,200 you see the most profound change and that is the emergence of the etheric
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.36,1:34:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,brain an energy brain composed only of energy no protoplasm that's the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.81,1:34:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulty of science and consciousness science and theology is they don't get
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.40,1:34:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's a major change there you can't explain consciousness in terms of
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.65,1:34:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,brain physiology all right so the etheric brain then very fast your
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.06,1:34:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,etheric prefrontal cortex is very fast and overlays the emotion so compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.32,1:34:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you see the self see the limitations of mankind is suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.97,1:34:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than as evil so instead of hating them you have a certain empathy I can
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.84,1:34:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,see how a person could be carried away by a certain emotion I can see that and
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.30,1:35:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see the rhetoric that's designed to do that in fact you know the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.15,1:35:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,political
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.92,1:35:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,has been to the argument is meant to bring up emotion and bypass your
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.61,1:35:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect all right so here the more evolved person so the left brain person
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.15,1:35:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely has a different physiology generally as well because he's always
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.22,1:35:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,releasing emergency emotions emergency emotions with consequences to the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.77,1:35:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,immune system and the balance of the acupuncture system
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.81,1:35:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,below above 200 then where we value truth for its own sake you now tend to
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.80,1:35:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,release endorphins and you see that information is processed differently this
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.42,1:35:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding this comprehension is primarily within the etheric brain the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.65,1:36:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,etheric brain to which the neurons resonate by induction the etheric brain
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.89,1:36:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's relationship to the neuron to me is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.06,1:36:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,analogous to a magnetic field creating electricity in a wire. A wire, if you move
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.89,1:36:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it back and forth through a magnetic field, will create electricity.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.28,1:36:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnetism doesn't move through the wire, you understand? So research on the nature
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.53,1:36:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness, which is always fixated on the neurons, they can't seem to get
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.07,1:36:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,off the neuron, it's because they're coming from the bottom up instead of the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.46,1:36:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,top down is why, from the contextual viewpoint, is because consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.48,1:36:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,dominates and it's the etheric brain then is like a magnetic field, the neuron
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.65,1:36:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a wire, and the ideation is a consequence of the influence of the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.60,1:37:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,etheric brain on the physical brain, which is also in compliance with the
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.02,1:37:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,observations of famous Nobel Prize winners
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.67,1:37:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that the
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.67,1:37:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,brain is a receiving instrument. The Buddha, you know, said there were six
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.30,1:37:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,senses and not man's traditional five and he conceived that the brain is a
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.89,1:37:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,receiving instrument for the mind. It's a receiving, a sensory, so the brain is a
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.90,1:37:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,sensory organ of thinkingness. So this major transformation here comes only
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.19,1:37:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,about through evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.88,1:37:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when it begins to value truth over the personal gain of the selfish ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.88,1:37:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,People think they're addicted to the world or attached to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.96,1:37:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.06,1:37:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not attached to the world at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.64,1:37:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're attached to the ego juice.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.19,1:38:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You get off your perceptions of the world to be right or to get even
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.85,1:38:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or to be rich or famous,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.92,1:38:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to have lots of followers, to be worshipped.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.22,1:38:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what you're attached to.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.82,1:38:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You're attached to just one thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.22,1:38:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that all these positionalities give you an ego juice.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.34,1:38:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only addicted to one thing, and that's the ego juice
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.02,1:38:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you get out of your positionalities,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.18,1:38:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which is important to know when we get to transcending the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.85,1:38:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,People think, oh, I can't overcome all these attractions to the world
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.30,1:38:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these lures and all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.00,1:38:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.68,1:38:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Think.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.38,1:38:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody would ever get enlightened if that was so.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.39,1:38:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't process multi-millions of data,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.13,1:38:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a great deal of which you've even forgotten is working unconsciously.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.89,1:38:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but you can let go and surrender to God the satisfaction
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.53,1:38:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that you get out of these ego positions
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.06,1:39:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of winning, of being right, of feeling sorry for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.65,1:39:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of being the martyr, of getting even, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.39,1:39:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.47,1:39:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the higher levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.39,1:39:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, what is this here?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.07,1:39:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, rates of happiness, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.61,1:39:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so as far as out there-ness,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.14,1:39:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see the ego thinks that happiness is derived
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.53,1:39:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from getting something from out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.69,1:39:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can see the more autonomous your state of happiness is,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.53,1:39:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it eventually doesn't depend on anything out there.
